    <main>
        <a href="/dashboard" class="back-button">Back to Dashboard</a>

        <section id="introduction">
            <h1>Introduction</h1>
            <p>The Admin Dashboard is a centralized management platform designed for administrators to monitor and
                manage key aspects of the application. It provides insights through analytics, control over user
                management, and settings configuration to ensure a smooth operational experience.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="system-requirements">
            <h2>System Requirements</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>OS: Ubuntu 22.04 or equivalent</li>
                <li>Database: MongoDB (version 8.0.3)</li>
                <li>Node.js: Version 20.18.0</li>
                <li>npm: Version 10.8.2</li>
                <li>Shell: Bash</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="installation-setup">
            <h2>Installation and Setup</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Clone the repository.</li>
                <li>Install dependencies using <code>npm install</code>.</li>
                <li>Start the server with <code>nodemon server.js</code>.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        <section id="features">
            <h2>Features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Analytics Dashboard</li>
                <li>User Management</li>
                <li>Content Management</li>
                <li>Settings and Configuration</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="user-roles-permissions">
            <h2>User Roles and Permissions</h2>
            <p>The dashboard supports various user roles, each with specific permissions:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Admin</strong>: Full access to all functionalities.</li>
                <li><strong>Editor</strong>: Can manage content but lacks access to settings.</li>
                <li><strong>Viewer</strong>: Read-only access.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="dashboard-components">
            <h2>Dashboard Components</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Sidebar: Navigation links to main sections.</li>
                <li>Analytics: Visual reports on system usage.</li>
                <li>User List: Manage users, roles, and permissions.</li>
                <li>Settings: Adjust application configurations.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="usage-guide">
            <h2>Usage Guide</h2>
            <p>Follow these steps to effectively use the Admin Dashboard:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Log in with your administrator credentials.</li>
                <li>Navigate through the sidebar to access different sections.</li>
                <li>Use analytics to monitor user activity and performance metrics.</li>
                <li>Manage users in the User List section.</li>
                <li>Configure settings in the Settings section as needed.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        <section id="customization">
            <h2>Customization</h2>
            <p>To customize the dashboard, modify the CSS and JavaScript files located in the <code>public</code>
                folder. Ensure all changes are tested before deployment.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="troubleshooting">
            <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Issue:</strong> Cannot connect to MongoDB.
                    <br><strong>Solution:</strong> Check if MongoDB service is running and verify the connection string.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Issue:</strong> Server crashes after a change.
                    <br><strong>Solution:</strong> Restart the server using <code>nodemon server.js</code>.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="faq">
            <h2>FAQ</h2>
            <p><strong>Q: How do I add a new user role?</strong><br>A: Update the user roles in the settings file and
                modify permissions in the roles management section.</p>
            <p><strong>Q: How can I reset my admin password?</strong><br>A: Use the password reset feature on the login
                page or contact support.</p>
        </section>
